.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-2-5::.
4 different games are played: mah-jongg, snooker, bridge, monopoly
The people use 4 different means of transport: tram, train, van, bus
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: basketball, cricket, golf, handball
1. the person who's sport is handball is between the person playing mah-jongg and the person playing snooker##2
2. the person who's sport is handball is the person playing monopoly##1
3. the person driving the van is on the far right##1
4. the person playing snooker is on the left of the person playing bridge##1
5. the person who's sport is basketball is on the right of the person who's sport is golf##1
6. the person who's sport is golf is on the right of the person driving the train##1
7. the person who's sport is handball is between the person who's sport is golf and the person driving the tram##2

.:: Answer ::.
|            |      1      |    2     |      3      |     4      |
| Game   | mah-jongg | monopoly      | snooker       | bridge   |
| Transport      | tram   | train  | bus | van     |
| Sport      | cricket     | handball | golf        | basketball |

